    "16604612272b74cc1f": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "1660461227266cb95c-0": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "#2 Suffer from headaches or migraines? You may suffer from phonophobia",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "1660461227266cb95c-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Phonophobia simply means an intolerance or <strong>hypersensitivity to sound,<\/strong>or a fear of loud noises. People who suffer from <strong>phonophobia <\/strong>can experience feelings of panic or discomfort in reaction to even moderately loud sounds. It’s one of the most common symptoms experienced by migraine sufferers. Certain noises can cause extreme discomfort while migraines are building up and during attacks. But even people who don’t suffer from migraines can experience stress headaches in reaction to sound, if they are <strong>sensitive to noise.<\/strong><\/p>"
          }
        },
        "b6b50ba2-ba34-4929-9818-326b6ce694c2": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "#3 Are there certain movements or gestures that calm you down? Maybe it’s sensitive hearing",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "1660461227266cb95c-0",
        "1660461227266cb95c-1",
        "b6b50ba2-ba34-4929-9818-326b6ce694c2"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "center",
        "content_alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "background-1",
        "full_width": true,
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 0
      }
    },
    "16581501774a32acf8": {
      "type": "loop-article-img-txt",
      "blocks": {
        "16581501770ad7ecad-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If you have <strong>ears sensitive to noise<\/strong>, certain movements or gestures can provide temporary relief. As a person on the spectrum I’m very familiar with a certain behavior called “stimming.” After all, autism often goes hand in hand with <strong>noise sensitivity<\/strong>.<\/p><p>Auditory stimming can take the form of humming, grunting, tapping on objects or ears, and finger-snapping, among others. <\/p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
        "b6d13c7c-ae41-4912-b692-bd1efbe55088": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "button_label": "More on noise sensitivity",
            "button_link": "https:\/\/www.loopearplugs.com\/pages\/noise-sensitivity",
            "button_bgcolor": "",
            "button_txtcolor": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "16581501770ad7ecad-1",
        "b6d13c7c-ae41-4912-b692-bd1efbe55088"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/symptoms_of_noise_sensitivity.jpg",
        "image_3": "shopify:\/\/shop_images\/symptoms_of_noise_sensitivity.jpg",
