    "16560502492171dd33": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "9cf025d1-5938-49bb-88c5-4141d8af1b5c": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "#6 People either yelling or whispering make you go nuts? You might suffer from misophonia",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "76ff5268-049f-4343-93b3-691311723d4c": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>A lot of people think that noise sensitivity means you can’t handle high volumes, but it can be about more than that. Some people can be heavily triggered by certain soft sounds too.<\/p><p>Someone leaning over to softly whisper in their ear or soft chewing can give people with <strong>misophonia <\/strong>a serious case of the heebie-jeebies. And people with <strong>phonophobia <\/strong>can have extreme nervous reactions to sounds in a range of volumes, from clanking pans to crackling plastic bags.<\/p><p>So if you’re wondering,<strong>“why am I so sensitive to noise<\/strong>that can’t actually damage my eardrums?” perhaps it’s a form of <strong>noise sensitivity.<\/strong><\/p>"
          }
        },
        "c17791aa-99c0-44b1-9c0e-b600e8c2dd36": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "#7 Feel more comfortable wearing headphones, anywhere you go? That could be noise sensitivity",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "16560502493ef96db8-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Are you someone who’s headphones are just about fused to your head? Whether you’re at work, the supermarket, or walking down the street? I totally get it, because as someone with <strong>autism <\/strong>I’m extremely sensitive to sound. For me it feels safer to pop in my <a href=\"https:\/\/www.loopearplugs.com\/products\/quiet\" target=\"_blank\">Loop Earplugs<\/a> or noise canceling headphones when I go outside!<\/p><p>So if you feel the need to filter out sound one way or another, guess what: it could be <strong>noisesensitivity<\/strong>.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
